<i>noun</i>: 홍조 [홍조] <i>verb</i>: 후끈후끈하다 [후끈후끈하다], 후끈하다 [후끈하다], 후끈대다 [후끈대다], 후끈거리다 [후끈거리다], 화끈화끈하다 [화끈화끈하다], 화끈하다 [화끈하다], 화끈대다 [화끈대다], 화끈거리다 [화끈거리다], 상기되다 [상ː기되다/상ː기뒈다], 붉히다 [불키다], 달다 [달ː다] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>홍조 [홍조]</dt><br>
<dd>1. sea glowing</dd><br>
<dd>아침 해가 바다에 비쳐 붉게 물든 경치.</dd><br>
<dd>A glow that shows when the sun radiates over the sea in the morning.</dd><br>
<dd>2. blush; flush</dd><br>
<dd>부끄럽거나 취하여 얼굴이 붉어짐. 또는 그런 빛.</dd><br>
<dd>A state in which a face is reddened from embarrassment or drunkenness; or such a color on the face.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>후끈후끈하다 [후끈후끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot or for one's face to suddenly feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>후끈하다 [후끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to become hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>후끈대다 [후끈대다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>후끈거리다 [후끈거리다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to feel hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화끈화끈하다 [화끈화끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화끈하다 [화끈하다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become hot or for one's face to become hot and turn red.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화끈대다 [화끈대다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>화끈거리다 [화끈거리다]</dt><br>
<dd>burn; glow; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열을 받아서 갑자기 뜨거워지거나 뜨거운 느낌이 일어나다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an object to become suddenly hot, being exposed to heat or for one's face to become suddenly hot and turn red, or to feel a surge of heat.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>상기되다 [상ː기되다/상ː기뒈다]</dt><br>
<dd>flush; glow</dd><br>
<dd>흥분하거나 부끄러워 얼굴이 붉어지다.</dd><br>
<dd>To blush because one is excited or embarrassed.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>붉히다 [불키다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. blush; flush</dd><br>
<dd>부끄럽거나 화가 나서 얼굴을 붉게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To make one's face red with shyness or anger.</dd><br>
<dd>2. redden</dd><br>
<dd>슬픔이나 감동으로 눈물이 나서 눈 주위를 붉게 하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To make one's eye rims red by dropping tears when one is sad or moved.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>달다 [달ː다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. heat up; become red-hot</dd><br>
<dd>쇠나 돌 등의 타지 않는 물체가 열을 받아 매우 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For an uninflammable thing such as metal and stone to be heated and become very hot.</dd><br>
<dd>2. blush; flush</dd><br>
<dd>열이 나거나 흥분되거나 또는 부끄러워서 얼굴이 뜨거워지다.</dd><br>
<dd>For one's face to become hot because one has a fever, or is excited or shy.</dd><br>
<dd>3. be impatient; fret</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 걱정이 되어 초조해 하고 불안해하다.</dd><br>
<dd>To feel nervous and anxious because one is concerned about something.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>